{"title_page": "Michael Pound", "text_new": "{{notability|Academics|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox academic\n| honorific_prefix   = <!-- see [[MOS:HONOURIFIC]] -->\n| name               = Michael Pound\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              = Michael-Pound.jpg\n| image_size         = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = Michael in 2018\n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| birth_name         = <!-- use only if different from full/othernames -->\n| birth_date         = <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}}  -->\n| birth_place        = \n| death_date         = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| region             = Nottingham, United Kingdom \n| nationality        = \n| citizenship        = \n| residence          = \n| other_names        = Mike Pound\n| occupation         = Lecturer, Researcher\n| period             = Present\n| known_for          = \n| title              = \n| boards             = <!--board or similar positions extraneous to main occupation-->\n| spouse             = \n| children           = \n| parents            =\n| relatives          =\n| awards             = <!--notable national level awards only-->\n| website            = \n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = <!--will often consist of the linked name of the last-attended higher education institution-->\n| thesis_title       = \n| thesis_url         = \n| thesis_year        = \n| school_tradition   = \n| doctoral_advisor   = \n| influences         = <!--must be referenced from a third party source-->\n| era                = \n| discipline         = [[Computer Science]]\n| sub_discipline     = Bioimage analysis, computer vision, image recognition, computer security<!--academic discipline specialist area \u2013 e.g. Sub-atomic research, 20th Century Danish specialist, Pauline research, Arcadian and Ugaritic specialist-->\n| workplaces         = University of Nottingham\n| doctoral_students  = <!--only those with WP articles-->\n| notable_students   = <!--only those with WP articles-->\n| main_interests     = \n| notable_works      = \n| notable_ideas      = \n| influenced         = <!--must be referenced from a third party source-->\n| signature          = \n| signature_alt      = \n| signature_size     = \n| footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Michael P. Pound''' is a researcher at the [[University of Nottingham]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Michael Pound |url=https://www.nottingham.ac.uk/biosciences/people/michael.pound |website=University of Nottingham |accessdate=2 September 2018}}</ref> He is known for his work in the areas of [[Bioimage informatics|bioimage analysis]], [[computer vision]], [[Facial recognition system|image recognition]], [[computer security]], his master courses within the [[Safari books online]] platform<ref>{{cite web |title=Exper Transport Layer Security - Live Online Training |url=https://learning.oreilly.com/live-training/courses/expert-transport-layer-security-tls/0636920369196/ |accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref>, and for his appearances on the video series ''Computerphile''<ref>{{cite web |title=Computerphile |url=https://www.youtube.com/user/Computerphile |website=YouTube}}</ref>.\n\n==Career==\nPound's work centres on the use of [[machine learning]], [[deep learning]], and bioimage analysis for the purpose of plant [[Phenotype|phenotyping]].<ref name=\"pw_security\" /><ref>{{Cite book |doi = 10.1109/ICCVW.2017.241|chapter = Deep Learning for Multi-task Plant Phenotyping|title = 2017 IEEE International Conference on Computer Vision Workshops (ICCVW)|pages = 2055\u20132063|year = 2017|last1 = Pound|first1 = Michael P.|last2 = Atkinson|first2 = Jonathan A.|last3 = Wells|first3 = Darren M.|last4 = Pridmore|first4 = Tony P.|last5 = French|first5 = Andrew P.|isbn = 978-1-5386-1034-3|chapter-url = http://eprints.nottingham.ac.uk/47610/1/Pound_Deep_Learning_for_ICCV_2017_paper.pdf}}</ref> His work on the identification of root and leaf tips through image-based phenotyping has been recognized as important in the field of bioimage analysis.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Atanbori |first1=John |last2=Chen |first2=Feng |last3=French |first3=Andrew |last4=Pridmore |first4=Tony |title=Towards Low-Cost Image-based Plant Phenotyping using Reduced-Parameter CNN. |pages=1 |url=https://www.plant-phenotyping.org/lw_resource/datapool/systemfiles/elements/files/42aa0773-949c-11e8-8a88-dead53a91d31/current/document/0023.pdf |accessdate=3 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe image analysis tool RootNav was developed by a research team led by Pound. The tool uses image analysis to identify complex root system architectures.<ref name=\"RootNav_Primary\">{{cite journal |last1=Pound |first1=Michael |last2=French |first2=Andrew |last3=Atkinson |first3=Jonathan |last4=Wells |first4=Darren |last5=Malcolm |first5=Bennet |last6=Pridmore |first6=Tony |title=RootNav: Navigating images of complex root architectures |journal=Plant Physiology |date=1 January 2013 |pages=113.221531 }}</ref> It has been made available to the scientific community and has been used by other researchers in the field to facilitate [[batch processing]] of high numbers of images in various studies of plant phenotyping.<ref name=\"phenotyping_and_beyond\">{{cite journal |last1=Granier |first1=Christine |last2=Vile |first2=Denis |title=Phenotyping and beyond: modelling the relationships between traits |journal=Current Opinion in Plant Biology |date=2014 |pages=96\u2013102 }}{{dead link|date=March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Media appearances==\nPound has made numerous appearances on [[Brady Haran]]'s video series ''Computerphile''. During these appearances, Pound has discussed aspects of his work including [[password cracking]], [[brute-force attack|brute forcing]], [[Kernel (image processing)#Convolution|kernel convolution]] and [[image analysis]].<ref name=\"photo_filters\">{{cite web |last1=Muller |first1=Tiffany |title=Listen to an Expert Image Analyst Easily Explain the Science Behind Photo Filters |url=https://www.diyphotography.net/listen-to-an-expert-image-analyst-easily-explain-the-science-behind-photo-filters/ |website=DIY Photography |accessdate=2 September 2018|date=2015-10-03 }}</ref><ref name=\"pw_security\">{{cite web |last1=Keeper Security |title=Keeper Q&A: What You Can Learn From Michael Pound's Scary Password-Cracking Video |url=https://keepersecurity.com/blog/2016/11/07/keeper-qa-what-you-can-learn-from-michael-pounds-scary-password-cracking-video/ |website=Keeper |publisher=Keeper Security, Inc |accessdate=2 September 2018|date=2016-11-07 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://twitter.com/_mikepound?lang=en Mike Pound - Twitter]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pound, Michael}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Computer programmers]]\n[[Category:Computer scientists]]\n[[Category:People associated with the University of Nottingham]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{notability|Academics|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox academic\n| honorific_prefix   = <!-- see [[MOS:HONOURIFIC]] -->\n| name               = Michael Pound\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              = Michael-Pound.jpg\n| image_size         = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = Michael in 2018\n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| birth_name         = <!-- use only if different from full/othernames -->\n| birth_date         = <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}}  -->\n| birth_place        = \n| death_date         = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| region             = Nottingham, United Kingdom \n| nationality        = \n| citizenship        = \n| residence          = \n| other_names        = Mike Pound\n| occupation         = Lecturer, Researcher\n| period             = Present\n| known_for          = 